  "notes": "Standard Mandarin (Pǔtōnghuà), Beijing-based. THIS SPEC READS PINYIN, NOT HANZI — its graphemes are Pinyin units and the input contract is Pinyin. Nothing here reads a Han character, and nothing could: a Han character does not encode sound, so no rule engine can pronounce one. That limit is stated by `zh-Hani`. Pinyin, being an alphabet, is fully transcribable — which is why the romanization is the tractable orthography and the native script is not. Going from Hanzi to this spec needs a dictionary (CC-CEDICT), not rules. Four lexical tones plus neutral.",
